.</i>480– <i>c.</i>550 ) who composed the Benedictine rule of Christian monastic life that is still followed in essence by all Western orders. He was born near Spoleto in Umbria, central Italy. After studying in Rome, he went to live as a hermit at Subiaco, and later organized groups of followers and imitators into monastic cells. In  <i>c.</i>529  he moved to Monte Cassino, where he founded the great monastery that is still the centre of the Benedictine order. His rule is simple, restrained, and practical.  See also  Bennett ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Bengt Bosson was born as the son of Bo NN and Mrs. Bo NN. He married Mrs. Ragnhild Bosson before 1292. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died before 1336."},"et":{"–before 1336":"–enne 1336","–1336":"–1336","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1240–1293":"1240–1293","about 1293":"umbes 1293","before 1336":"enne 1336","1336":"1336","1240":"1240","1293":"1293","before 1292":"enne 1292","about 1240":"umbes 1240","Sweden":"Rootsi"},"fi":{"–before 1336":"–ennen vuotta 1336","–1336":"–1336","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1240–1293":"1240–1293","about 1293":"noin 1293","before 1336":"ennen vuotta 1336","1336":"1336","1240":"1240","1293":"1293","before 1292":"ennen vuotta 1292","about 1240":"noin 1240","Sweden":"Ruotsi"},"fr":{"–before 1336":"–avant 1336","–1336":"–1336","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1240–1293":"1240–1293","about 1293":"environ 1293","before 1336":"avant 1336","1336":"1336","1240":"1240","1293":"1293","before 1292":"avant 1292","about 1240":"environ 1240","Sweden":"Suède","lifeSummary":"Bengt Bosson est né, fils de Bo NN et Mrs. Bo NN. Il a épousé Mrs. Ragnhild Bosson avant 1292. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 2 filles. Il est décédé avant 1336."},"de":{"–before 1336":"–vor 1336","–1336":"–1336","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1240–1293":"1240–1293","about 1293":"um 1293","before 1336":"vor 1336","1336":"1336","1240":"1240","1293":"1293","before 1292":"vor 129